This paper is about deep neural network compression, which is a topic that falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for machine learning tasks and proposes a compression algorithm for these networks. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper evaluates the algorithm on several image datasets. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for AI tasks and proposes a compression algorithm for these networks. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper discusses the use of neural networks and proposes a compression algorithm for these networks. The fifth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes a new algorithm for compressing neural networks.
